<p class="lead">(rewrite)The sticky nav is only used for linking within a page to in-page content. It appears below the normal navigation bar and affixes to the top of the browser window as you scroll down past it. The sticky nav also highlights the current section as you scroll down the page.</p>

<h2>(rewrite)Rules for the sticky nav</h2>

<ul>
    <li>Must add the CSS <code>position: relative;</code> to the <code>body</code> for section highlighting to work.</li>
    <li>Must only be used on long pages where there is a need to provide a quick means of navigating between sections.</li>
    <li>Must come below the page intro so that it is clear it is secondary navigation only related to the page content.</li>
    <li>Must not contain any dropdown menus.</li>
    <li>Must only contain links to in-page content.</li>
    <li>Must not display on more than one row.</li>
    <li>Only one per page.</li>
</ul>
<h2>(rewrite)Quirks</h2>
<ul>
    <li>If at bottom of the page then automatically jumps to last item.</li>
    <li>Watchout for tabbing up.</li>
    <li>Have suffiecient space for offset.</li>
</ul>

